title: Sidewall, "Diagonal Floral", 1935–45
description: Design composed of diagonal lines of flowering vines criss-crossing one another and forming horizontal diamonds containing a balanced lace-like design. Original taken from house built in late 17th century in Williamsburg. This is an approved Colonial Williamsburg reproduction. Printed in margin: "Katzenbach and Warren, Diagonal Floral, No. 221."

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, "Diagonal Floral", 1935–45.
1935–45. Machine-printed. Gift of William E. Katzenbach. 1946-18-2.
